                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d937">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Eddy</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-10-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 6, 1901</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Adee states that the secretary of the mission board telegraphs that the
                    money needed for Miss Stone’s ransom will undoubtedly be <pb facs="1089"
                        n="1009" xml:id="pg_1009"/> raised by popular subscription, which is already
                    begun; that Mr. Eddy’s efforts are warmly approved; that Russian cooperation,
                    especially at Sofia, is most valuable and is cordially welcomed, as is also the
                    weighty aid of the other ambassadors.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
